We contribute to the overall goal of transparent and safer ML models in the following ways:
We propose a new regression method (DNNR) that performs on par with state-of-the-art algorithms; DNNR is theoretically grounded: we provide a proof to bound DNNR s point-wise error (Theorem 1) and validate its usefulness empirically;
An extensive evaluation against 11 methods on a set of 8 regression datasets, the PMLB benchmark (133 datasets), and Feynman symbolic regression (119 datasets); We provide detailed analyses to understand DNNR s performance (ablation study; impact of data properties) and transparency (inspection of failure cases).
